The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 4: Shareholders of Mukesh Ambani-led Reliance Industries (RIL) met today in an extraordinary general meeting to vote on the merger of its subsidiary Reliance Petroleum with the company. The result of the voting will be announced on Monday, an RIL spokesperson said. Equity shareholders and secured and unsecured creditors of RIL took part in the meeting and voted on the merger proposal, the official said.                            
	 Mumbai, April 4: The countrys forex reserves declined $1.5 billion to $252.32 billion for the week ended March 27 compared with $253.82 billion a week ago. During the period, the foreign currency assets were $241.59 billion, down $1.64 billion, against $243.23 billion in the previous week, the Reserve Bank of India said in its weekly report.                             
	 London, April 4: General Motors will move ahead with the bankruptcy process at a faster pace if it becomes necessary to restructure the auto maker, its new chief executive Fritz Henderson said. He would prefer an out-of-court restructuring for GM.                                                                                                                           
